'''CNS''' may refer to: {{TOC right}}
==Science and medicine== * ''[[Cell (journal)|Cell]]'', ''[[Nature (journal)|Nature]]'', and ''[[Science (journal)|Science]]'', three of the most prestigious scientific journals involved in biomedical research * [[Central nervous system]], brain and spinal cord * [[Clinical nurse specialist]] * [[Coagulase-negative staphylococcus]], term to describe all ''staphylococcus'' species that are not ''staphylococcus aureus'' * [[Computational neuroscience]] * [[Conserved non-coding sequence]], a region of DNA that is conserved through evolution and does not code for proteins * [[Crigler–Najjar syndrome]], rare hereditary disease * [[Crystallography and NMR system]], software library for computational structural biology * [[Thiocyanate]], an organic compound in the cyanate family * [[Color Naming System]]
==Military== * [[Chief of the Naval Staff (disambiguation)|Chief of the Naval Staff]], the formal title for the commander of and highest-ranking officer in the navies of various countries, including: **Chief of the Naval Staff and [[Commander of the Royal Canadian Navy]], Canada **[[Chief of the Naval Staff (India)]] **[[Chief of Naval Staff (Pakistan)]] * Abbreviation for "Chinese Navy Ship": **used unofficially as a prefix before the [[Ship prefix|names of ships]] of China's [[People's Liberation Army Navy]]; see [[List of active People's Liberation Army Navy ships]] **Formerly used by [[Republic of China Navy|Taiwanese navy]] ships; occasionally still used unofficially by third parties as an exonym
==Education== * [[Cicero-North Syracuse High School]] in Cicero, New York * [[City of Norwich School]], a secondary school in Norwich, England * [[Computation and Neural Systems]], a Ph.D. option at [[Caltech]]
==Organisations== * [[Canadian Nuclear Society]], technical society of the Canadian Nuclear Association * [[Congress of Neurological Surgeons]], a professional society representing neurosurgeons * Corporation for National Service, former name of the [[Corporation for National and Community Service]], an independent agency of the United States government * [[Council for National Security]], military regime that governed Thailand following the 2006 coup d'état * [[Szekler National Council]] (''Consiliul Naţional Secuiesc''), an organization representing the ethnic Szeklers of Romania

===Internet=== * [[Cybercast News Service]]

===Sport=== * [[Campeonato Nacional de Seniores]], a football club competition in Portugal
